line_1: That love shall vainer loves expel,
line_2: O let thy fear within me dwell,

line_1: And Love, with thy great Antidote, expel:
line_2: I'll bid these tender silly things Farewel;

line_1: Tho' cruel Hand the banish'd Wretch expell,
line_2: And force the Captive from his native Cell,

line_1: To strengthen Sinews, and Catarrhs expel,
line_2: And none for Colicks cou'd her Art excel.

line_1: Lest some fond nymph your pleasures all expel.
line_2: None ever yet did mother Eve excel.

line_1: Drive thence the Passions, and the Guilt expel,
line_2: And call fair Virtue to the polish'd Cell.

line_1: And till Aurora shou'd the shades expel,
line_2: Implor'd a lodging in her friendly cell.
